# Testing Conventions

Use Vitest. Run with `npm run test`.

## What to test

| Code type | Test approach |
|-----------|---------------|
| Pure helpers (`*-utils.ts`, formatters, mappers) | Direct unit tests, no mocks |
| Validation and error branches | Unit tests with explicit inputs |
| Async orchestrators (routes, `search.ts`, upload pipeline) | Mock external IO; assert calls and returned shape |
| Real external behaviour (PDF parse, HTTP) | Optional `*.integration.test.ts` |

Add or update tests when changing logic in `src/lib/`, `src/app/api/`, and non-trivial hooks.

## File naming

- Unit tests: colocate as `foo.test.ts` next to `foo.ts`
- Integration tests: `foo.integration.test.ts` when real network/files are required
- Do not put test files in React components unless testing component behaviour

## Pure function tests

```typescript
// src/lib/rag/search-utils.test.ts
import { mergeWithRrf } from '@/lib/rag/search-utils';

it('boosts chunks that appear in both result lists', () => {
  const merged = mergeWithRrf(vectorResults, keywordResults);
  expect(merged[0].chunkId).toBe('b');
});
```

Prefer table-driven cases for edge conditions (empty input, short queries, sanitisation).

## IO orchestration tests

Mock at module boundaries (`@/env`, `@/lib/supabase/admin`, `fetch`, third-party parsers). Use `vi.hoisted()` when mock factories need shared spies.

```typescript
const { rpcMock } = vi.hoisted(() => ({ rpcMock: vi.fn() }));
vi.mock('@/lib/supabase/admin', () => ({
  createAdminClient: () => ({ rpc: rpcMock }),
}));
```

Test behaviour, not implementation details: returned data, thrown errors, and which external calls were made.

## Coverage expectations

- New pure helpers: tests required
- Bug fixes: add a regression test when practical
- UI-only copy/layout tweaks: tests optional
- Do not add tests that only restate TypeScript types or trivial getters

## Before finishing

Run `npm run test`, `npm run typecheck`, and `npm run lint`.
